cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a model for non-autoregressive sequence generation using generative flow, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks to model complex distributions, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the model on neural machine translation (NMT) datasets, which involves processing and understanding natural language, making cs.CL and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves generating sequences of tokens, which can be applied to image captioning and other computer vision tasks.
